        ],
        [
          "Intelligent Tutoring System",
          "E-Learning",
          "Content-Based Filtering",
          "Exercises",
          "4163 ASSIST09 learners, 1452 Intelligence18 learners",
          "Mathematics and English language courses",
          "Exercise Sequence, Knowledge Components",
          "The contextualized Q-Matrix (CQ-Matrix) is initialized by a combination of learner historical performance and expert opinions. ",
          "Each student as a set of knowledge vectors that are updated after each interaction.\n\nCold-start is handled by a “global” Knowledge Vector.",
          "Logs are cleaned for missing or invalid KC mappings. \n\nThe weighted Q-Matrix is converted into a contextualized CQ-Matrix.",
          "Top-N Exercises",
          "{Top-N Precision: 0.40 - LSTMCQP - up to 80 items}",
          "Authors use a Knowledge Tracing Model which serves as a foundation for a Recommender System.\n\nThe main idea is that, by identifying areas where the student is “having difficulties” and make recommendations to address that.",
          "- No pre-requisite relationships between KCs. \n\n- Context is limited to performance-derived factors.\n\n- Offline validation on 2 datasets.\n"
        ]
      ],
      "index": 7
    },
    {
      "block_id": "1ce4750c-f3ba-8049-a47c-c3c65a113e20",
      "heading": "Summary Table REC",
      "rows": [
        [
          "Task",
          "Context",
          "Student Performance Definition",
          "Target",
          "Students",
          "Courses",
          "Data sources",
          "Features",
          "Flaw of Previous Models",
          "Novelty of Model",
          "Preprocessing Details",
          "Models",
          "Assessment Strategy",
          "Performance Metric: Best Model",
          "Comments",
          "Limitations"
        ],
        [
          "Classification",
          "Intelligent Tutoring System",
          "Next Exercise Correctedness",
          "Probability of Answering Correctly",
          "4163 ASSIST09 learners, 1452 Intelligence18 learners",
          "Mathematics and English language courses",
          "Exercise Sequence, Knowledge Components",
          "[Sequence of Exercises taken, Expert Derived Q-Matrices] ",
          "Most DKT approaches are unable to fulfiil the promise of personalization without the need of adding new features - which defeats the purpose of “simpler models*.",
          "Authors propose the introduction of CQ-Matrix that is not derived from experts but instead from data. \n\nThis CQ-Matrix is integrated into a DKT framework with LSTM (and a personalization layer) to ensure better personalization of exercises and content.  ",
          "Logs are cleaned for missing or invalid KC mappings. \n\nThe weighted Q-Matrix is converted into a contextualized CQ-Matrix.",
          "BKT, DKT, CBQM, CBQC, LSTMCQ, LSTMCQP",
          "5-Fold Cross-Validation",
          "AST09\n{AUC: 0.7388 - LSTMCQP, RMSE: 0.4189 - LSTMCQP}\n\nIntellilence18\n{AUC: 0.6896 - LSTMCQP, RMSE: 0.3173 - LSTMCQP}",
          "The authors propose 2 distinct algorithms for the task of KT. \n\nCBCQ is a content-based algorithm while LSTMCQP is a deep-learning based approach. \n\nAuthors test both of these models against other common baselines and find that LSTMCQP tends perform better both in terrms of RMSE and AUC. \n\nThe study does not feature an ablation study to check the influence of each component.",
          "- No ablation study\n\n- Only tests against BKT and DKT as baselines (missing other relevant architectures) \n\n- No consideration of relationships between Knowledge Components\n\n-  Only 2 datasets are used. \n\n- KC mastery is determined by performance without considering the text of the exercises. "
        ]
      ],
      "index": 9
    }
  ],
