    {
      "id": "1914750c-f3ba-80a7-a2bc-e095b4591549",
      "type": "paragraph",
      "text": "ITS require good KT in order to effectively estimate students’ needs and recommend approapriate content. BKT and DKT are popular KT techniques. One of the main problems with these approaches is that KC are treated as independent entities (which is an unreasonable assumption). Authors present two approaches that contextualize KC:",
